  serving size: 615
---

Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @sweet potato{1%unit} into 1cm chunks (no need to peel) and pop them onto a large #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil for cooking{1/2%tbsp}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the middle shelf until golden and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Pop a deep #saucepan{} (with a tight-fitting #lid{}) on medium heat with the oil (see pantry for amount). When hot, add the garlic and stir-fry for ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @jasmine rice{150%grams} until coated, ~{1%minute}. Add @salt{1/4%tsp} and the @water for the rice{300%ml} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pot from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

In the meantime, lay the @salmon fillets{2%unit}, skin-side down, onto another lined medium baking tray. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Pop the salmon onto the top shelf of your oven until cooked through, ~{10-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw fish. It's cooked when opaque in the middle.

While everything's in the oven, trim the @baby cucumber{1%unit}, then pop onto a #board{} and use a #rolling pin{} to gently smack it a few times until split. Cut into roughly 2cm chunks.

In a medium #bowl{}, combine the @sambal paste{15%grams}, @rice vinegar{15%ml} and @sugar for the dressing{1%tsp} (see pantry for amount). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Add the cucumber into the dressing and mix together. Set aside.

A few mins before everything's ready, pop a small saucepan on medium heat.

Add the @gochujang paste{50%grams}, @honey{15%grams} and @butter for the sauce{30%grams} (see pantry for amount).

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, put the sachet in a bowl of hot water for 1 min to loosen.

Stir vigorously until the butter has melted and the sauce is piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}. Remove from the heat.

Share the rice between your serving bowls.

Top the rice with the salmon, sweet potato and smacked cucumber in separate sections. Spoon the gochujang butter sauce over the fish (reheat first if needed) and drizzle over any remaining dressing over the cucumber.

Drizzle over the @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} (see pantry for amount) and sprinkle with the @black sesame seeds{5%grams} to finish.

Enjoy!